 Ed Sheeran and Cherry Seaborn Ed Sheeran has announced the birth of his second child with his wife Cherry Seaborn. The Bad Habits singer and his wife Cherry Seaborn have welcomed a new baby girl into their family becoming once again a parent to two girls. The Perfect crooner shared the good news on his social media accounts. Ed and Cherry have already given birth to a daughter. They are now a family of four. Ed Sheeran posted an image of socks on his Instagram account, which was precisely like the first time they revealed they were expecting a baby girl.
Sheeran in his Instagram post wrote, “Want to let you all know we’ve had another beautiful baby girl. We are both so in love with her, and over the moon to be a family of 4 x.” Ed and Cherry married in a small wedding with about 40 guests in February 2019. Ed announced the birth of their first daughter in August 2020 in a similar way where he wrote, “Ello! A quick message from me as I have some personal news that I wanted to share with you. Last week, with the help of an amazing delivery team, Cherry gave birth to our beautiful and healthy daughter – Lyra Antarctica Seaborn Sheeran. We are completely in love with her. Both mum and baby are doing amazing and we are on cloud nine over here. We hope that you can respect our privacy at this time. Lots of love and I’ll see you when it’s time to come back, Ed x.”